ues than Scala's built-in Enumeration. It provides the compile-time macro implementations that discover enum entries and validate value enums, avoiding runtime reflection while keeping enum definitions concise.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/index.json:18:      \\\"enumeratum\\\"\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/$version$/enumeratum-circe_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/lloydmeta/enumeratum\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:7:    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/lloydmeta/enumeratum/tree/enumeratum-$version$/enumeratum-circe/src/test/scala\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/$version$/enumeratum-circe_3-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Enumeratum is a type-safe, reflection-free enumeration library for Scala, and enumeratum-circe adds Circe encoders, decoders, and key codecs for its enum and value enum types. It lets Scala 3 JVM applications serialize and deserialize Enumeratum entries as JSON strings or primitive values while reusing Circe's standard type class APIs.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum-circe_3/index.json:18:      \\\"enumeratum\\\"\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/beachape/enumeratum_3/$version$/enumeratum_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/lloydmeta/enumeratum\\\",\\n./metadata/com.beachape/enumeratum_3/index.json:7:    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https: