sting ValueOfFromExprProbe, tweaking it to create Ident using quotes more accurately.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering code organization**\\\\n\\\\nI need to think about cleaning up some code. Perhaps I could remove unused imports like Type Expr Quotes if there's no probe. Also, I wonder if I should remove the main build if it’s not necessary. It looks like src/main needs to exist, but keeping it is essential. If there’s no main in Scala, I know the priority should be on the main. I also need to ensure Yretain-trees compiles both main and runtime.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_yQjBWlK7PP5IjvD1yoXrzER0|fc_05c8c20709c6133c0169fb991e6a548197a5f96e7fc9390e37\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacrosTest.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\nimport scala.quoted.Expr\\nimport scala.quoted.Quotes\\nimport scala.quoted.Type\\n\", \"newText\": \"import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"          |import com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3.MediumPriority\\n          |import com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3.Priority\\n          |import com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3.ValueEnumMacrosFieldGetProbe\\n          |import enumeratum.ValueEnumMacros\\n\", \"newText\": \"          |import com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3.MediumPriority\\n          |import com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3.Priority\\n          |import enumeratum.ValueEnumMacros\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"          |  val valueSum: Int = values.map(_.value).sum\\n          |  val hasExpectedOrder: Boolean =\\n          |    values == IndexedSeq(LowPriority, MediumPriority, HighPriority)\\n          |  val reachedFieldGet: Boolean = ValueEnumMacrosFieldGetProbe.reachesFieldGe